USA}}||align=center|2003\u20132006\n|-\n||[[Johan Offermans]]||align=center|{{flagicon|NED}}||align=center|2007\u20132014\n|-\n||[[Peter Hall (sailor)|Peter Hall]]||align=center|{{flagicon|CAN}}||align=center|2015\u20132016\n|-\n||[[Michael Dietzel]]||align=center|{{flagicon|GER}}||align=center|2017\u2013Present\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Rules ===\nThe ISA rule set consist of the following documents:\n* WS INTERNATIONAL SOLING CLASS RULES<ref name=\"ClassRules\" />\n* ISA Constitution<ref name=\"ISA\" />\n* ISA Championship rules<ref name=\"ChampionshipRules\" />\n* ISA Ranking Ruling<ref name=\"RankingRuling\" />\n* ISA Standard Notice Of Race<ref name=\"SNOR\" />\n* ISA Standard Sailing Instructions<ref name=\"SSI\" />\n* ISA Permitted Instruments<ref name=\"PermittedInstruments\" />\n* ISA Championship Agreement Form<ref name=\"ChampionshipAgreementForm\" />\n\n== National Soling Associations ==\nIn 2019 there are 24 NSAs active and there are three countries with individual fleets. Since 1968 over fifty countries (not counting the no longer existing countries like the [[USSR]], [[Yugoslavia]] and [[East-Germany]]).<ref name=\"NSA\" /> \n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n|style=\"vertical-align:top\"|'''Current<br>NSAs'''\n|style=\"vertical-align:top\"|\n  {{Collapsible list\n    |framestyle  = border:none; padding:0;\n    | title      = Africa&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n    | bullets    = on\n    | 1          = {{flagicon|RSA}} South Africa National Soling\n  }}  \n|style=\"vertical-align:top\"|\n  {{Collapsible list\n    |framestyle  = border:none; padding:0;\n    | title      = Asia&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n    | bullets    = on\n    | 1          = {{flagicon|JPN}} Japan Soling Association \n  }}  \n|style=\"vertical-align:top\"|\n  {{Collapsible list\n    |framestyle  = border:none; padding:0;\n    | title      = Australasia&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;